<!--hvy: {"id":"hvy-format-reference","editorOnly":true}-->
#! HVY Format Reference

<!--hvy:text {"id":"hvy-format-return-contract"}-->
 Return raw HVY for exactly one complete section. Do not return document front matter, Markdown fences, tool JSON, HTML, JSX, or explanatory prose.

<!--hvy:text {"id":"hvy-format-core-rules"}-->
 Core syntax rules:
 - HVY directives are HTML comments: `<!--hvy:component-name {...json...}-->`.
 - Directive payloads are single-line valid JSON objects.
 - Indentation is structural. Child blocks are indented under the section or parent block.
 - Section titles use `#!`; ordinary Markdown headings such as `##` are text content, not sections.
 - Use stable, lowercase, hyphenated ids for sections and xref-worthy records.

<!--hvy: {"id":"hvy-format-section-example","tags":"example"}-->
