    Expandable content requires a content slot.

<!--hvy: {"id":"hvy-format-template-rules"}-->
#! Reusable Template Rules

<!--hvy:text {"id":"template-rules-text"}-->
 - Preserve useful component names from the matched template instead of replacing structured records with plain text.
 - Preserve template fields like `sortKeys`, `groupKeys`, `tags`, and xref metadata when they fit the imported data.
 - Remove filled template placeholder state such as `hideIfUnmodified` from generated sections that contain imported content.
 - Custom components from the matched template use the same directive form, for example `<!--hvy:skill-record {...}-->` or `<!--hvy:history-record {...}-->`.

<!--hvy: {"id":"hvy-format-xref-rules"}-->
#! Xref Rules

<!--hvy:text {"id":"xref-rules-text"}-->
 - `xrefTitle` is required on xref-card.
 - `xrefTarget` should be an exact id from the relationship inventory. Do not invent a target id just to make a link.
 - Do not create reciprocal/generated xref cards by hand; document update scripts may generate those after the section is applied.
